      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "Issue #6582 is closed and locked, this is an update should it help any others. \r\n[https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/issues/6582](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/issues/6582)\r\n\r\nThe issue  is `npm start` returns HTTP 400  when large headers are sent to the service. \r\nI hit this issue using OpenID-Connect, an Oauth2 extension. Others have with large JWT headers. \r\n\r\nThe correct work-around was nearly noted in #6582.   \r\nThe correct work around is to update `package.json` to\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  ...\r\n  \"scripts\": {\r\n         react-scripts  --max-http-header-size=77777 start\r\n         ...\r\n   }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nto set max headers to 77,777 bytes, as example. \r\nThis overrides node.js server with the same. \r\n\r\nThe original now locked issue has the syntax slightly out in terms of order and missing a `=` operand. \r\n\r\n"
