      "body": "UI from dev mode and prod mode look different because, if I'm not mistaken, the project initially created by `create-react-app` and built by `npm run build` seems to ignore nested css calc() functions and the math calculations in it when I inspect the component of the two different modes: <br>\r\n<br>\r\nIn the original `src`, it says:<br>\r\n`.switch:after {\r\n  width: calc((var(--size) / 2) - calc(var(--indent) * 2));\r\n}`<br><br>\r\nbut when I inspect the built (deployed) web UI, it shows:<br>\r\n`.switch:after {\r\n  width: calc((--size) - var(--indent));\r\n}`<br>\r\nof course the UI looks different from the development mode.\r\n<br><br>\r\nmy `react` version is `16.12.0` and `create-react-app` version is `3.3.0`<br>\r\nalso `node` version is `v10.15.0` and `npm` version is `6.4.1`"
