      "body": "### Describe the bug\r\nnode version: v8.11.4\r\nnpm version: 5.6.0\r\ncreate-react-app version: 3.3.0\r\n\r\nsteps:\r\n\r\n1. create-react-app demo\r\n2. cd demo\r\n3. npm run eject\r\n4. add one folder named **s1** and create App.js, App.css in s1.\r\ns1/App.js :\r\n```\r\nimport React from 'react';\r\nimport './App.css';\r\nclass App extends React.Component {\r\n    constructor(props) {\r\n        super(props);\r\n        this.state={};\r\n    }\r\n    componentDidMount() {\r\n\r\n    }\r\n    render() {\r\n        return (<p className=\"s1\">s1</p>);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\nexport default App;\r\n```\r\nand the default src/App.js:\r\n```\r\nimport S1 from './s1/App';\r\nimport './App.css';\r\nconst A=(props)=>{\r\n    return <a>\r\n        <S1></S1>\r\n    </a>\r\n}\r\nexport  default A;\r\n```\r\n\r\nnote that we have imported two **App.css** of the same name while in different folders.\r\n5. then do **npm run build**\r\nWe can find that the css .map file shows that only one App.css was 'loaded' in the sources below(without the file's path):\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10143629/72161421-0ad8a700-33fb-11ea-8fd1-37e69415afe8.png)\r\nAs a result, we can not position at the correct source code of css when we need in our web browser. If we click this:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10143629/72162040-2ee8b800-33fc-11ea-9df9-40cad0d9c0da.png)\r\nwe will see  the irrelevant code which is the other one App.css.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10143629/72162243-8c7d0480-33fc-11ea-9cd0-8fb6195c1597.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n"
