      "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nnpm throws warnings about sass-loader missing peer dependencies\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\n```\r\nnode --version && npm --version\r\nv12.1.0\r\n6.13.4\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nRun `npm install react-scripts`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nnpm should not throw errors or warnings.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n```\r\nnpm WARN sass-loader@8.0.0 requires a peer of node-sass@^4.0.0 but none is installed. You must install peer dependencies yourself.\r\nnpm WARN sass-loader@8.0.0 requires a peer of sass@^1.3.0 but none is installed. You must install peer dependencies yourself.\r\nnpm WARN sass-loader@8.0.0 requires a peer of fibers@>= 3.1.0 but none is installed. You must install peer dependencies yourself.\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nAccording to the [docs](https://create-react-app.dev/docs/adding-a-sass-stylesheet/), `node-sass` should be installed separately. Since that is the case, then `sass-loader` should be an optional dependency or only installed if it finds node-sass.\r\n"
