      "body": "This PR fixes the importLoaders setting for sass files. I believe this was broken in #5829 when an additional loader was introduced but the `importLoaders` setting was not incremented.\r\n\r\nI ran into this trying to upgrade react-scripts locally. Verified this change fixes it for our project.\r\n\r\nThis is the error I ran into:\r\n```\r\nError: resolve-url-loader: CSS error\r\n  file:///MySassFile.module.scss:42:6: Unknown word\r\nYou tried to parse SCSS with the standard CSS parser; try again with the postcss-scss parser\r\n  You tried to parse SCSS with the standard CSS parser; try again with the postcss-scss parser\r\n    at runMicrotasks (<anonymous>)\r\n```"
