      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "### Is your proposal related to a problem?\r\n\r\nWhen creating a react app with a template that include a dependency requiring a git repo to work, the installation can fail or be incorrect for the developer that executes create-react-app on their machine. This is because the [git repo is initialized after template dependencies are installed](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/blob/master/packages/react-scripts/scripts/init.js#L268).\r\n\r\nAn example is a very popular package [husky](https://github.com/typicode/husky) which adds git hooks to `.git` directory as part of its postinstall scripts. Those hooks won't be added for the person setting up the app with `npx create-react-app ...`\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\n- split [tryGitInit()](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/blob/master/packages/react-scripts/scripts/init.js#L44) into 2 separate functions - one that initializes the repo, second that creates commit.\r\n-  move execution of the first function up, possible at the beginning of main [`init.js function`](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/blob/master/packages/react-scripts/scripts/init.js#L85)\r\n\r\nIf you are OK with the proposed solution I'll be happy to prepare PR with the implementation.\r\n"
